# Data

This folder contains de-identified behavioral and questionnaire data
supporting the analyses in the manuscript.

## Files

| File | Description | Used in |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `likability.csv` | Per-participant likability ratings (1–7) for high- and low-livingness images, plus Connectedness to Nature scores | Figure 5 |
| `livingness.csv` | Per-participant perceived livingness ratings (1–7), structured as above | Figure 5 |
| `forced_choice.csv` | Per-participant forced-choice preferences for high- vs. low-livingness images | Figure 3 |
| `subjective_ratings.csv` | Aggregated mean ratings (likability, livingness, complexity) per image pair | Figure 2 |
| `aesthetic_emotions.csv` | Mean ratings for the 7 aesthetic emotion categories | Figure 4 |
| `questionnaires.csv` | Pre-scan questionnaire scores (EIBES, CNS, AEQ, etc.) | SI Table S14 |
| `stimuli_metadata.csv` | Image IDs, AI-derived livingness scores, and category labels | Methods |

## Notes

- All ratings are on a 7-point Likert scale unless noted.
- Image IDs follow the convention `[Group][Pair][a/b]`, where 'a' = high livingness and 'b' = low livingness.
- Participant IDs are anonymous codes; no demographic information is included.
- Missing values are coded as blank cells.
